usage: wikireader.py [-h] [-m {terse,summary,full,random}] [-n] [-d] [-t]
                     [article [article ...]]

positional arguments:
  article               the name of the article you want to read

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -m {terse,summary,full,random}, --mode {terse,summary,full,random}
  -n, --news            displays the latest headlines
  -d, --didyouknow      displays some interesting facts
  -t, --today           displays noteworthy events that occurred on this date
